immagine dell\'avatar nella schermata dettaglio ordine Venere bottone per effettuare un acquisto Painted by Sandro Botticelli between 1482-1485, and exposed at the Galleria degli uffizi in Florence, The Birth of Venus is an artwork made of Tempera and alabaster powder on canvas depicting the myth of the birth of the goddess Venus from the sea foam.\n
David Van Gogh The Scream Sculpted by Michelangelo Buonarroti between 1501–1504, and exposed at the Galleria dell\'Accademia in Florence, David is a marble sculpture portraying the biblical hero preparing to face Goliath the giant.\n Painted by Vincent Van Gogh in 1889, and exposed at the Musée d\'Orsay in Paris, Van Gogh\'s self portrait is an artwork made of oil on canvas.\n Vincent often presented himself as restrained and serious in his self-portraits, with a look of concentration on his face.\n Painted by Edvard Munch in 1893, and exposed at the National Gallery in Oslo, The Scream is an artwork made of oil, tempera, pastel and crayon on cardboard symbolizing the anxiety of the human condition.\n
